# DermaTriage

A mobile-first web app that lets users take a photo of their skin with their iPhone camera and receive a cautious, AI-powered triage assessment.

## Stack
- Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4
- OpenAI GPT-4o-mini for image analysis (`app/api/analyze/route.ts`)
- Supabase optional for auth/database/storage (`lib/supabase.ts`)
- Deployed on Vercel

## Key files
- `app/page.tsx` — main UI, handles capture + results
- `components/CameraCapture.tsx` — camera preview, capture, retake/confirm
- `app/api/analyze/route.ts` — OpenAI vision analysis endpoint
- `lib/supabase.ts` — Supabase client (only initialised when env vars present)

## Rules
- Keep the UI mobile-first, simple, and high-contrast.
- Never expose `OPENAI_API_KEY` client-side; route all analysis through the API.
- Always include the medical disclaimer: this is not a diagnosis.
- Use Vercel Preview Deployments for every branch; disable Preview Deployment Authentication in Vercel project settings.
- Prefer functional React components and TypeScript strict types.
